  "prompt": "When is best time to meditate?",
  "response": "The best time to meditate varies depending on individual schedules and preferences, but here are some generally recommended times:\n\n1. Morning\n- Early morning, right after waking up\n- Mind is fresh and less cluttered\n- Sets a positive tone for the day\n- Before breakfast or daily responsibilities\n\n2. Before bed\n- Helps calm the mind\n- Reduces stress and improves sleep quality\n- Can help with relaxation and letting go of daily tensions\n\n3. Mid-day\n- During lunch break\n- Helps reset and recharge\n- Can reduce midday stress and increase afternoon productivity\n\n4. Whenever you can consistently practice\n- The most important factor is consistency\n- Choose a time you can stick to regularly\n- Find a time that fits your personal schedule and energy levels\n\n5. When you feel stressed or overwhelmed\n- Can be done anytime you need to center yourself\n- Helps manage immediate emotional states\n\nTips:\n- Start with short sessions (5-10 minutes)\n- Experiment to find what works best for you\n- Create a consistent routine\n- Choose a quiet, comfortable space\n\nRemember, there's no universally \"perfect\" time - the best time is when you can meditate consistently and comfortably.",
